<p>Select the three statements needed to calculate the value of x in the following:
<br />
\( x = \sqrt{y^2 + z^2} \)
<br />
For this exercise, calculate \(y^2\) before \(z^2\).</p>

<zyQ>
<zyQText> First statement is:  </zyQText>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns> temp1 = Math.pow(x , 2.0);</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>x doesn't need to be squared.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>

<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns> temp1 = Math.pow(z , 3.0);</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl> z needs to be squared, not cubed. </zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>

<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns> temp1 = Math.pow(y , 2.0); </zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Statement assigns y squared to temp1.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>

<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns> temp1 = Math.sqrt(y);</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl> The square root of y is not needed. </zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText> Second statement is:  </zyQText>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns> temp2 = Math.sqrt(x , 2.0);</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>The Math.sqrt() method takes only 1 argument.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>

<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns> temp2 = Math.pow(z , 2.0);</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Statement assigns z squared to temp2.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>

<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns> temp2 = Math.pow(z);</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl> The Math.pow() method requires two arguments. </zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>

<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns> temp2 = x + Math.sqrt(temp1 + temp2);</zyQAns>
